Phenolics exist widely in nature as natural products, and they possess multiple biological properties (
Kling et al., 2014
). As one of the most typical botanic phenolics, gallic acid is commonly used in the esterification reaction of many bioactive compounds (
Karas et al., 2017
). The galloylation of phenolics could significantly change their biological activities. These compounds were usually reported to exhibit better activity compared with the parent molecule. (
Lewandowska et al., 2016
). 

Archidendron clypearia
(Jack) I.C.Nielsen.

is a tree widely distributed in many areas of tropical Asia (
Li et al., 2004
). Systematic phytochemical studies led to the discovery of diverse structures including polyphenols, flavonoids, lignans and terpenoids (
Thao et al., 2016
; 
Wang et al., 2017
, 2018). Among them, various 
types
of galloyl substituted phenolics are the most characteristic constituents of this plant, and some of them have been reported with high potential for neurodegenerative treatments (
Gaudreault and Mousseau, 2019
; 
Marinelli et al., 2016
; 
Williams et al., 2011
).

Oxidative stress has been generally considered as one of the major causes of the neurodegenerative diseases (
Block et al., 2002
; 
Sosa et al., 2013
). Excessive free radicals in the body can damage various biomolecules including protein, lipid and nucleic acids, leading to cellular function disorder and apoptosis (
Zhang et al., 2011b
). Therefore, it is of utmost importance to explore anti-oxidative candidates to quench the elevated ROS and alleviate the symptoms of neurodegeneration conditions. As part of a continuous investigation of the twigs and leaves of 
A. clypearia
, five undescribed galloylated phenolics (
1–5
) together with thirteen known ones (
6–18
) were isolated and identified. All isolates were tested for their protective effects to reverse H 
2
O 
2
-induced damage in human neuroblastoma SH-SY5Y cells. In addition, the possible mechanism of the top three potent compounds (
1–3
) were also investigated in this study.

Thirteen known compounds were determined based on comparison of their spectroscopic data with those in the literature. They were identified as (2 
R
,3 
R
)-catechin-7- 
O
-gallate (
6
) (
Mahmood et al., 1993
), (2 
R
,3 
R
)-gallocatechin-7- 
O
-gallate (
7
) (
Bao et al., 2009
), 5-methoxygallocatechin (
8
) (
Vercauteren, 2009
), (2 
R
,3 
S
)-gallocatechin-4′- 
O
- gallate (
9
) (
Lee et al., 1992
), isookanin (
10
) (
Han et al., 2016
), 5′-hydroxyeriodictyol (
11
) (
Fan et al., 2017
), 7,3′,4′-trihydroxyflavone (
12
) (
Shi et al., 2017
), myricetin (
13
) (
Zhang et al., 2018
), melanoxetin (
14
) (
Bodede et al., 2018
), 7-methoxymelanoxetin (
15
) (
Clark-Lewis and Porter, 1972
), falloconvolin B (
16
) (
Zhang et al., 2011a
), 3,4,5-trimethoxyphenol-1- 
O -β
-D-(6′- 
O
-galloyl)glucopyranoside (
17
) (
Tian et al., 2015
) and phlorizin (
18
) (
Zhang et al., 2012
).
